    <div id="res761257714" class="bucketwrap bookedition">
      <h6><a href="https://www.npr.org/books/titles/761257700/gun-island">Gun Island</a></h6>
   <p class="author">by <a href="https://www.npr.org/books/authors/137958124/amitav-ghosh"><span>Amitav Ghosh</span></a></p>   <div class="bookinfo">
            <p>Hardcover, 313 pages <span class="pipe">|</span></p>      <a href="#" class="purchase" data-metrics='{"category":"Ecommerce","action":"Click purchase book"}' >purchase</a>      <div class="ecommercepop">
                  <div class="ecomm_body">
                        <button class='btn-close'>close overlay</button>            <h3>Buy Featured Book</h3>
            <dl class="meta"><dt>Title</dt><dd>Gun Island</dd><dt>Author</dt><dd>Amitav Ghosh</dd></dl>            <input type="hidden" id="ecommerceId" value="3" />
            <p class="support">Your purchase helps support NPR programming. <a href="https://help.npr.org/customer/portal/articles/2168887-how-can-my-online-purchases-support-npr-programming">How?</a></p>            <ul class="purchase-links">
                              <li><a  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Amazon","category":"Ecommerce","label":"9780374167394"}'  class="buylink1" href="https://www.amazon.com/Gun-Island-Novel-Amitav-Ghosh/dp/0374167397?SubscriptionId=AKIAIZJ4UUS4DXXBCGJQ&tag=npr-5-20&linkCode=xm2&camp=2025&creative=165953&creativeASIN=0374167397">Amazon</a></li>
               <li><a  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Independent Booksellers","category":"Ecommerce","label":"9780374167394"}'  class="buyLink3" href="http://www.indiebound.org/book/9780374167394?aff=NPR">Independent Booksellers</a></li>
            </ul>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="ECOMM_BODY" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="ECOMMERCEPOP" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END CLASS="BOOKINFO" -->
</div>

<!-- END ID="RES761257714" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP BOOKEDITION" -->

</div>   <p>In 2016, Amitav Ghosh was working on his novel <em>Gun Island,</em> and imagined a scene in which a wildfire was advancing toward a Los Angeles museum. About six months later, that scenario played out in real life, as <a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/12/06/568760424/california-wildfires-spread-spurred-on-by-strong-winds">the Skirball fire burned</a> near The Getty Center in December 2017. Ghosh says he felt "completely shaken."</p>   <p>"To see things that you've seen in your mind sort of playing out in real life — it's just so disturbing you know?" he says. "But that is the world that we are in. The world of fact is outrunning the world of fiction."</p>   <p>Ghosh believes old legends have a lot to teach us about how to think about the cataclysmic effects of climate change. "Fiction allows us to look at the world in a different way," he says. "And I think that is really the crisis of contemporary fiction: that it finds itself — at this catastrophic time for humanity — it finds itself unable to look at the reality around us."</p>   <p>Ghosh often sets his own fiction at the blurry boundary between land and water. His latest novel stops in several of those places — from mangrove islands on the border of India and Bangladesh to the canals of Venice, Italy. <em>Gun Island</em> is a modern retelling of a Bengali myth that Ghosh grew up with. The goddess at the center of this myth is named Manasa Devi and she's not just a goddess — she's also a sort of interpreter, connecting humans to the natural world.</p>   <aside id="ad-backstage-wrap" aria-label="advertisement">
    

    <div id="ad-backstage-Arts___Life_Books_Author_Interviews" class="ad-backstage" data-ad-config='{"network":"\/6735\/","site":{"default":"n6735.NPR","mobile":"n6735.NPRMOBILE"},"zone":"Arts___Life_Books_Author_Interviews","targets":{"testserver":"false","isPodcastEpisode":"false","storyId":"761257295","program":"All_Things_Considered","book_genres":["Nonfiction","Historical_Fiction","Fiction","Science___Health"]},"location":"backstage","deferred":false,"isBetweenContent":true,"isAggSponsorship":false,"borderClass":""}'></div>

</aside>   <div class="hr"><hr></div>   <h3 class="edTag">Interview Highlights</h3>   <p><strong>On Manasa Devi</strong></p>   <div id="res761290592" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage697699971" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/27/697699971/when-everything-is-changing-stories-have-a-role-to-play"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/27\/697699971\/when-everything-is-changing-stories-have-a-role-to-play"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/25/cover-663x1024_sq-4bc22d0559aaede1d4793d95fe7778f146204b9d-s100-c15.jpeg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/25/cover-663x1024_sq-4bc22d0559aaede1d4793d95fe7778f146204b9d-s100.jpeg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="When 'Everything' Is Changing, Stories Have A Role To Play" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/book-reviews/">Book Reviews </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/27/697699971/when-everything-is-changing-stories-have-a-role-to-play"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/27\/697699971\/when-everything-is-changing-stories-have-a-role-to-play"}' >When 'Everything' Is Changing, Stories Have A Role To Play</a></h3>
         </div>
         
